HEADWORD: Formyl
<hw>For"myl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Form</ets>ic +
<ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A univalent
radical, <chform>H.C:O</chform>, regarded as the essential residue of
<xex>formic</xex> acid and aldehyde.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Formerly,
the radical methyl, <chform>CH3</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

